The `remaining` property should calculate the time left before the timeout expires. If no timeout is set (i.e., `self._timeout` is None), it should return None. If the timeout has already expired (i.e., `self._cancelled` is True), it should return 0.0. Otherwise, it should subtract the current loop time from the scheduled cancellation time (`self._cancel_at`).

```
def remaining (self) -> Optional[float] :
    if self._timeout is None:
        return None
    if self._cancelled:
        return 0.0
    if self._cancel_at is not None:
        return max(0.0, self._cancel_at - self._loop.time())
    return self._timeout
